# orcasecurity_integration_monday_resource (Data Source)

Looks up an existing Monday.com credentials resource (the entity managed by the
[`orcasecurity_integration_monday_resource`](../resources/integration_monday_resource.md)
resource) by its human-friendly `name`.

Common reasons to use this data source instead of creating the resource:

* Credentials were created in the Orca UI and you want to attach Terraform-managed
  templates to them.
* Credentials live in a different Terraform workspace.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/orcasecurity_integration_monday_resource/data-source.tf"}}

## Argument Reference

* `name` — (Required, String) Human-friendly name of the existing Monday.com resource.
  The data source fails if zero or more than one resource match.

## Attribute Reference

* `id` — (String) Orca resource identifier (UUID). Feed this into the `resource_id`
  argument on `orcasecurity_integration_monday_template`.
* `account_slug` — (String) Monday.com account slug stored on the resource.
